  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Lucia Weston describes the 4th of July celebration at the Chardon Street Chapel and comments on the behavior of Rev. John Pierpont. [See Ms.A.9.2 v.11, p.130 for the 4th of July celebration program of the Boston Anti-Slavery Society.] She tells about social gatherings and viewing the fireworks in the Boston Common. Francis Jackson was impersonated in a farce called the &quot;Retired Soap-Boiler,&quot; which &quot;has reference to his actions in regard to the License law.&quot;</subfield>
